## Framework

This project uses **MC Framework** for authentication, access, and environment provisioning.

@mc-framework/AGENTS.md

Read AGENTS.md to understand:

- Which `mc` commands are available (open, shell, dev, auth status, logout, destroy)
- How auth and access work in this isolated WSL model
- Why MCP servers run inside the distro (and how the stdio bridge works)
- When to ask vs. when to execute

For Power Platform / Dataverse / Code Apps / Power Automate / etc. development questions
that are NOT covered by MC Framework, the agent should consult:
- The `microsoft-learn` MCP (already wired in `.mcp.json`)
- [microsoft/PowerAppsCodeApps](https://github.com/microsoft/PowerAppsCodeApps) samples
- [microsoft/power-platform-skills](https://github.com/microsoft/power-platform-skills) (the official Claude plugin, optionally installed)
- Its own general knowledge / reasoning

## Quick commands

```powershell
mc open {{DISTRO}}     # open VS Code Remote-WSL
mc shell {{DISTRO}}    # interactive shell inside the distro
mc dev {{DISTRO}}      # convenience: npm install && npm run dev
mc auth status {{DISTRO}}   # check pac/az auth state
mc logout {{DISTRO}}   # logout at end of day
```

